{
text "f1-01" "Shell Sort" at (120,50) color black font SansSerif size 32 bold
}
{
text "f1-02a" "Insertion Sort is slow, because it can only move elements" at (20,100) color black font SansSerif size 24
text "f1-02b" "one position to the right with each step.                   " at (20,130) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
{
text "f1-03a" "Shellsort tries to move elements faster to their final position " at (20,170) color black font SansSerif size 24
text "f1-03b" "by using leaps.                                              " at (20,200) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
{
text "f1-04a" "The data is h-sorted in each step. A set of data is  " at (20,240) color black font SansSerif size 24
text "f1-04b" "h-sorted, if selecting every h-th element starting at position 0,..., h-1  " at (20,270) color black font SansSerif size 24
text "f1-04c" "will always yield a sorted data set.     " at (20,300) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
{
text "f1-05a" "Therefore, a h-sorted array consists of h independently sorted" at (20,340) color black font SansSerif size 24
text "f1-05b" "data sets interleaved in one array                                " at (20,370) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
{
text "f1-06a" "To sort the data, Shell Sort performs a set of h-sorting steps   " at (20,410) color black font SansSerif size 24
text "f1-06b" "for decreasing values of h, until it finally performs h-sorting for h==1.      " at (20,440) color black font SansSerif size 24
text "f1-06c" "h==1 essentially equals Insertion Sort.             " at (20,470) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
{
text "f1-07a" "The set of values to use for h is also called the increment order.   " at (20,510) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
