{
text "f2-01" "Verbal Description" at (120,50) color black font SansSerif size 32 bold
}
{
text "f2-02a" "It can be proved, that h[i+1]=3*h[i]+1 yields good results.         " at (20,100) color black font SansSerif size 24
text "f2-02b" "Using this, the algorithm can be adapted as follows:" at (20,130) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
{
text "f2-03" "1. while h<=n/9, set h=3*h+1                                      " at (20,200) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
{
text "f2-04" "2. Set i=h                                                          " at (20,240) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
{
text "f2-05a" "3. Store Element a[i] in a variable v, and store i in j   " at (20,280) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
{
text "f2-06" "4. While j>h ist and a[j-h]>v, set a[j]=a[j-h] and j=j-h          " at (20,350) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
{
text "f2-07" "5. Set a[j]=v                                                       " at (20,390) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
{
text "f2-08" "6. Increment i. If i<n, continue with step 3          " at (20,430) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
{
text "f2-09" "7. Set h=h/3 (integer division!). If h>0, continue with step 2" at (20,470) color black font SansSerif size 24
}
